            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>The LESSEE agrees to comply with the following enhanced terms and conditions:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>1. Purpose of Use:</strong> The facility shall be used solely for the purpose specified in the approved request. Any changes to the intended use must be communicated and approved by COA-CAR.</li>
                    <li><strong>2. Time Management:</strong> The LESSEE shall strictly adhere to the allocated time as stated in their approved request. Any extension or adjustment to the allotted time must be requested in advance and approved by COA-CAR.</li>
                    <li><strong>3. Footwear Policy:</strong> Only rubber shoes are permitted in the playing area. Leather shoes, ladiesâ€™ sandals/heels, hiking shoes, spiked shoes, and similar footwear are not allowed to maintain the safety and condition of the facility.</li>
                    <li><strong>4. Sports Equipment:</strong> The LESSEE is responsible for providing their own sports equipment such as basketballs, volleyballs, volleyball nets, badminton rackets, and badminton nets. COA-CAR does not provide these items.</li>
                    <li><strong>5. Damage and Loss:</strong> The LESSEE shall immediately report any damage, destruction, or loss of amenities and equipment used in the Multi-Purpose Building to Mr. Renante Fecha, Section Chief, and General Services Unit. The LESSEE will be held accountable for any resulting expenses or replacement costs.</li>
                    <li><strong>6. Maintenance and Cleanliness:</strong> The LESSEE is responsible for maintaining order and cleanliness within the premises at all times. Any waste, debris, or personal belongings must be properly disposed of or removed from the facility after use.</li>
                    <li><strong>7. Liability:</strong> COA-CAR shall not be held responsible for any injuries, accidents, or untoward incidents that may occur during the activity. The LESSEE assumes full liability for their actions and the actions of their participants.</li>
                    <li><strong>8. Prohibited Substances:</strong> The consumption of liquor or any intoxicated beverages/drinks is strictly prohibited within the premises. Individuals under the influence of alcohol or drugs are not allowed to enter or engage in any activities within the facility.</li>
                    <li><strong>9. Cooperation with Security:</strong> The LESSEE must cooperate with the security agency employed by COA-CAR to ensure compliance with the agency's policies on discipline, cleanliness, and sanitation while within the vicinity of the COA-CAR premises.</li>
                    <li><strong>10. Compliance with Terms and Conditions:</strong> The LESSEE acknowledges and agrees to abide by all the aforementioned terms and conditions throughout their use of the Multi-Purpose Building.</li>
                    <li><strong>11. Violation Consequences:</strong> Failure to comply with any of the above terms and conditions may result in denial of similar requests from the LESSEE and the Organization/ Institution/ Team/ Establishment/ Group where the LESSEE is affiliated.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>By accepting these terms and conditions, the LESSEE acknowledges his/her understanding and commitment to adhere to the rules established by COA-CAR for the proper and responsible use of the Multi-Purpose Building.</p>
